    <subfield code="y">00001 (Color online) Occupation numbers $n_J$ (\ref{rho_diag}) and pair emission amplitudes $s_J$ (\ref{kappa_diag}) in calcium isotopes ($A$ is the mass number). The solid lines show the shell-model results (by NuShellX), using the FPD6 single-particle energies and pairing two-body matrix elements. The symbols show the GDM results, where black circles, blue up-triangles, green squares, and red down-triangles are for single-particle levels $f_{7/2}$, $p_{3/2}$, $f_{5/2}$, and $p_{1/2}$, respectively. The same color convention is used in plotting the solid lines (shell).</subfield>
